        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(write): add renameIdentity option for FUSE mounts with unstable inode numbers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add explicit `renameIdentity: \"verify-content-with-lock\"` compatibility writes for rclone-style FUSE mounts whose destination inode changes across rename.\n- Keep strict `(dev, ino)` verification as the unchanged default.\n- Verify matching content under a cooperative lock only for the rename boundary; keep subsequent path identity checks strict.\n\nCloses #32.\n\n## Security contract\n\nThis is an explicit weaker opt-in for trusted/cooperating writers. It does not prove that the destination still names the temp-file object, retain the Python helper's fd-relative parent pinning, or stop a same-UID writer that ignores the advisory lock.\n\nThe compatibility lock is a per-target, SHA-256-keyed sidecar stored in the already-canonical root. That avoids creating a lock through a missing or raced target parent. Stale locks fail closed and are never reclaimed from host-local PID evidence. The stricter Python helper is deliberately bypassed only in this mode because it requires rename to preserve inode identity.\n\n## Implementation\n\n- Export `RenameIdentityPolicy` through the root API.\n- Add SHA-256 verification when the source temp fd and renamed destination report different identities.\n- Preserve strict defaults, `already-exists`, `mkdir: false`, stale-lock, and post-write identity behavior.\n- Document the compatibility boundary and add an `0.4.1 - Unreleased` changelog entry thanking @jlautman.\n- Add deterministic regressions for strict/compatible identity behavior, content replacement, per-call overrides, required-Python routing, create semantics, missing parents, stale locks, and normal POSIX cleanup.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm check`: 38 test files passed; 423 tests passed, 3 skipped.\n- `pnpm audit --prod --json`: 0 vulnerabilities.\n- Autoreview: no accepted/actionable findings after fixing the no-`mkdir` contract and lock-parent boundary findings.\n- Live packaged-consumer proof on AWS Crabbox, Ubuntu 26.04, kernel 7.0, Node 24.18.0, pnpm 11.9.0, rclone 1.74.3: [run `run_b2ca73c0818e`](https://crabbox.openclaw.ai/portal/runs/run_b2ca73c0818e), lease `cbx_dfc891eea183`.\n  - rclone rename identity changed from `55:13142417776620928161` to `55:13160412383924634112`.\n  - Strict mode returned `path-mismatch`.\n  - Compatibility mode wrote and read `compatible-content`.\n  - Root-level compatibility lock was absent after completion.\n\nExact validated head: `46e6cc26cba0f4f2b6e1ea5217cb35a6d34e1bd9`.\n",
